cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper proposes a novel architecture for text generation using images as input, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, as it generates text based on extracted features from images, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
